text.section:
The Secretary shall:
Administer this title and the rules and regulations adopted under this title;
Develop comprehensive policies and programs to evaluate, determine, and lessen hazards that are associated with the use of radiation;
Advise, consult, and cooperate with:
Experts in the field of radiation control;
Other agencies of this State;
The federal government;
Other states;
Interstate agencies;
Affected groups;
Affected political subdivisions; and
Affected industries;
Accept and administer, according to law, any available loans, grants, and other funds or gifts for carrying out the Secretary's powers and duties under this title;
Collect and publish health education information about protection from radiation hazards;
Review all radiation source plans and specifications that are submitted under the rules and regulations adopted under this title;
Inspect, to determine any possible radiation hazard:
Sources of radiation;
The shielding and immediate surroundings of radiation sources; and
Any records that concern the operation of radiation sources; and
Keep in confidence all information about commercial and industrial processes that is obtained in carrying out this title.
